 cafe's  and  bad  coffee sound of records on the jukebox smell of pie
 and ice cream the rhythm of the ride he could run with  the  best  of
 them  popping  those  little white pills and clicking off the miles a
 million pounds of steel right up against his back she sat  on  a  bus
 bench  and  adjusted  her  black high heel shoe another night of fake
