 held  the  gun  under a worn Navaho rug a bottle resting at his right
 foot the sun had finished making its way down in a bath  of  purplish
 and  orange  sauce his eyes now adjusted to the on coming darkness he
 sat and waited waited for Death to come he had never given up without
 a  fight  before and he wasn't about to this time never mind the fact
 that even now he had no idea what life was about or why  people  were
 put  in  the  world filled with so little joy and way too much sorrow
 and the funny thing as the older he had gotten the less he understood
